node.text: @veelanii
Yuman!

Are you simply yourself, the entire universe, or the very force that brings it all into existence?

Join leading AI researcher, Joscha Bach as he delves into the origins of consciousness and self-awareness – from infancy to adulthood – and what this reveals about the possibility of artificial intelligence achieving consciousness in the future.

Tap the link in bio to watch this talk in full.

@drakoumel_c that doesn't seem to reflect our intuitions about the body. We understand the neurons in the brain can't exist by themselves and the body can keep living without all the neurons in action. But it's the neurons that are processing certain levels of consciousness. Still we identify with all of the cells and not just the neurons. Humans are like a type of neuron processing a level of experience

this is the new religion. the arrogance of human that they believe they are the center of everything. he is very right as to how this self becomes self aware and creates it's own persona the "ghost in the shell". however we are not the generator we are far to small. don't be arrogant like western religions in which depict the human as the center of the world. we are here as a side effect of the cosmos. be happy that we exist enjoy it.
@bonoboschmidt *I have three children myself...

I remember back until being 2 years old, and I never talked about me in 3rd person since that. Maybe before, I can't remember between starting to talk and 2 years old. But claiming "between 2 and 5 children talk about themselves in 3rd person" is just not true. I have the children myself and also don't remember them talking about themselves in 3rd person.
@mateusz.kurkowski those were some big leaps indeed
@mateusz.kurkowski it's actually written about in the Vedas and Upanishads. So it's thousands of years old. You just don't know things. That's ok. 👍
@joshuasweeny also Plato said that we come to this world with all the knowledge of the universe and start to forget it ad we get old
This is a philosophical stance  called "jumping to conclusions"
@durisvk2 So you disagree that your eyes just send electrical signals to the brain that are then interpreted? Not proven by science?

Did you ever think that this is absolutely not provable by science? Plus, when we try to teach a toddler his/her name we usually refer to them in third person and that’s why they start talking in third person about themselves? Did you ever think about origins of human kind with no existing verbal language but the same consciousness we posses of? This is from scientifical perspective same level as flat earth - same amount of  evidence (0), trying to attract likes by finding a controversy (👍) - at least it’s less harmful so congrats to at least that
@anekemuthep gonna try to remember that one. You got more?
@anekemuthep can you elaborate on that last part? Im a bit lost on the singularity points and godels vessel

@el_dirtydan simply put: in the sum of each view and perceptions, when you are aware of being part of it, you can see what makes you unique, singular, a singularitiy point in terms of a unit of collective perception that becomes self-percibed; but the paradox of self perception is that, even using the perceptive elements and views of others and yours constructed, you cannot percibe all but your interpetation of the whole, and thats why i said that we are a Godelian vessel: because of Kurt Gödel's theory on the limits of mathematical knowledge which can extend to human knowledge: the fact that you cant know all the working of a system by using its limited rules, we cant pretend to know our construction by using the same rules that we are made. Hope all of this witten has clarify my point, at least i did my best :) alien promise 👽

This reminds me a famous quote atributed to James Clerk Maxwell "the only laws of mattee ar those wich our mind must fabricate, and the only laws of mind are fabricated by matter". That recurssive characterization make the experience of being a calideoscope of viewis in wich looking at it is alredy an exerercise of awarnes of our limits and the singularitiy points that makes us human as a whole being and ilusion in the same Gödel's vessel.
@timevoyager it's amazing is the same for everyone
@timevoyager you can actually have all those shrooms experiences by just meditating. No drugs needed. Mushrooms simply activate that function in the brain. But it's there before the drugs.
@veelanii
This is how you know shrooms were good.
@kubik.papik bullshitting
@kubik.papik exactly
Spiritual enlightenment explained under a minute 👏
@williammitchell99 being a “good image” is a forever unattainable goal. The goalposts can always move
And what should I do with that information? Work on being a good image first then you can worry about being the creator of the universe
@iridescent_ivy a great summary 👍.

Based upon this short out of context it’s easy to believe he’s advocating for Idealism, but he’s not. He’s using analogy to describe the processes that arise due to computation and change within our central nervous system. Meaning that reality as we understand is just an internally constructed world model trained through infancy by a former agent akin to a training algorithm. Ultimately to be subsumed by a self referential primary agent that we identify with.
@lezerkrisztus I'm with you here. I don't know the guy, so maybe he is smart, but the stuff he claims in this video here is really nonsense.
@alex_foly facts!
@journeyofnow whoever reads this check out joscha bach with Curt Jaimungal https://youtu.be/3MNBxfrmfmI?si=BR2DAdbqlssoQy4a
This guy is a legend. Look him up. He drops the craziest knowledge bombs that make you think for weeks.
@kiranrajrajappan a completely unprovable statement.
Yeah interpretation may vary from mind to mind. But reality is what it is. Simulation or not. God bless the scientists in Jesus's name and may he bring good wisdom.
@breezybrent we back to playing the game🙌
It was fun when we knew we were just playing a game
They are just seeing parallels with the ways we are thinking. Ain’t no code to crack
@maxeisenstich Never say never
We cracked the code millennia ago my friend

Are you f***in telling me they are about to crack the code of consciousness? I mean i knew AI is gonna go wild...But if this is possible, we are in for a wild ride...If AI is truly conscious, my oh my this world will be 1000 times more interesting...maybe a million times...

@simonsbookclub Hehe, it's most certainly not. But honestly it's far too much to unpick in the comments of an Instagram post. But essentially body functions are a result of consciousness. Why would inanimate matter just start wanting to stay animated (alive)? It wouldn't. It would need a purpose, a reason, or what's the point? What's the end goal? Any way, as I said, check out Anil Seth's work and even Rupert Sheldrake's work. 💪🏾😊

@phenikxmusic I’ll agree to disagree here. I’ve read Seth and had him autograph my Being You copy when I watched his lectures. He suggests physicalism. I’m inspired by epiphenomenolism, which isn’t tooooo far off. While I think people who support consciousness-first reasoning are doing so from a place of ego, and a desire for specialness, a fear of death, and a desire to connect with some mystic power, which is just religion smuggling its way into science. But that’s just my standpoint.

@simonsbookclub I respect your standpoint, sir. To me, it doesn't make sense that matter decided (an act of a conscious thing) to suddenly animate itself, because they would need a purpose (another phenomenon of something that's conscious) to do it. Matter, on its own, has no reason to keep itself sustained in any way. You feel hungry so you eat. Why do you need to eat? To live. Why do you need to live? You don't. A rock doesn't care if it's a rock or not, because it's inanimate. Water doesn't care if it's water or steam, because it's inanimate. But things with any level of consciousness do care (care being yet another thing of consciousness). Seems logical to me. But again, I respect your standpoint 🤷🏾‍♂️😊
Aren't the organism's interests the result of its own consciousness though?
@ritualtattoogibraltar unfortunately the charlatans sound like the actual
@ritualtattoogibraltar try mushrooms and see for yourself
I've tried everything 😜😈🤣🤣🤣
Sounds like just another pseudo-spiritual charlatan. 🙄
@cheri_boy pain is just one half of a descriptive feeling. Pleasure would not be without.
Funny how as a baby you couldn't generate electricity or heat to not be painful😂
@projectsatyaloka Exactly 💯💯
what does that mean
@calibri_govde a sanskrit term which means I am Brahman. Brahman is the Ultimate Reality in Hinduism which is defined as Consciousness.
Basically, "Aham Brahmāsmi"
@greysclublondon welcome. You have officially ascended
@greysclublondon Some toddler phase trauma freeze
@greysclublondon you had one “f” too many, it’s institute o fart!
So I still can’t get beyond this being the institute of fart. That’s where I’m at.
The body is the universe and the universe is the body. There is no clear distinction
Does he think he exists in his body in the universe?
@moritz.wiener 👆
A video of Darryl Anka would be amazing
@creativa_gestoso applies to all researchers…
@maxeisenstich AI researchers are paving the way to their own destruction... I call this the Golem Complex.
@creativa_gestoso Again like every researcher… Can’t stop evolution
The big problem with AI researchers is that they believe they understand what they are doing.
Damn I thought I was just crazy
But the judge didn’t go for that?

caption.text:
Are you simply yourself, the entire universe, or the very force that brings it all into existence?

Join leading AI researcher, Joscha Bach as he delves into the origins of consciousness and self-awareness – from infancy to adulthood – and what this reveals about the possibility of artificial intelligence achieving consciousness in the future.

Tap the link in bio to watch this talk in full.
